			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"><span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="text-decoration: underline">Veil of Abandon</span> [Cost: 6]</span>
<br />

<br />
Type: Activated, Refresh Time: 0:12:00 [Casting Time: 0:00:12]
<br />
Requirements: Level 63, No previous ability requirements.
<br />
This ability conjures a mystical portal causing all NPCs to forget about you. If you are out of immediate combat, this ability will also make you invisible. This ability is usable any time that you have 500 mana, provided refresh time has been met.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
The above is based upon the spell, 'Call of the Hero' and the bard AA, 'Fading Memories.'
<br />

<br />
Basically, the purpose of this AA is to be a self-only Call of the Hero type spell which effectively relinquishes the caster of all aggro, then providing that they evaded harm, they will be cloaked in a Veil of the Elements.
<br />

<br />
Obviously this would be exploitable if it was an instant-cast ability, so it will abide by the same limitations of Call of the Hero; 12 seconds casting time, one pearl required as a reagent, and 500 mana per cast.
<br />

<br />
Refresh time is loosely based on the 'Call of the Hero' spell, scaling one minute for each second of the original spell (12 minutes refresh vs. 12 seconds refresh). This will help prevent unintended use, such as using it to be a primary pulling class.
<br />

<br />
The cost of the ability itself, and the level requirement are both based on the 'Fading Memories' AA to help scale any balancing issues.
<br />

<br />
Please add any comments as you see fit.<br />_________________<br /><center><span style="font-size: 9px; line-height: normal">::: <b>Master</b> | <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=90407" target="_blank">Odibil Lauxes</a> | <b>Arch Convoker</b> :::<br>That which ordinary men are fit for, I am qualified in;<br>and within the best of me is <a href="http://www.diligenceguild.com" target="_blank">DILIGENCE</a>.</span></center></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
