			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Odibil Lauxes wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"><span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="text-decoration: underline">Veil of Abandon</span> [Cost: 6]</span>
<br />

<br />
Type: Activated, Refresh Time: 0:12:00 [Casting Time: 0:00:12]
<br />
Requirements: Level 63, No previous ability requirements.
<br />
This ability conjures a mystical portal causing all NPCs to forget about you. If you are out of immediate combat, this ability will also make you invisible. This ability is usable any time that you have 500 mana, provided refresh time has been met.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
The above is based upon the spell, 'Call of the Hero' and the bard AA, 'Fading Memories.'
<br />

<br />
Basically, the purpose of this AA is to be a self-only Call of the Hero type spell which effectively relinquishes the caster of all aggro, then providing that they evaded harm, they will be cloaked in a Veil of the Elements.
<br />

<br />
Obviously this would be exploitable if it was an instant-cast ability, so it will abide by the same limitations of Call of the Hero; 12 seconds casting time, one pearl required as a reagent, and 500 mana per cast.
<br />

<br />
Refresh time is loosely based on the 'Call of the Hero' spell, scaling one minute for each second of the original spell (12 minutes refresh vs. 12 seconds refresh). This will help prevent unintended use, such as using it to be a primary pulling class.
<br />

<br />
The cost of the ability itself, and the level requirement are both based on the 'Fading Memories' AA to help scale any balancing issues.
<br />

<br />
Please add any comments as you see fit.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
400-450 mana, and less cast time, and toss the pearl.  5 pp for a jolt spell is too much, though it's slightly more powerful in REMOVING the mage from the hate list, not just lowering it a fixed amount.  Like Izudin says, aggro is really only an issue in Tier 3+ PoP, and stuff there hits like freight trains...with tractor-trailers attached.  You're not going to have time to get it off you in 12 sec, you'll be dead or off the top anyways in 12 sec.  Making this worthless for it's intended purpose.
<br />

<br />
Being in a LDoN dungeon, with quad 400 hitters, and being told they don't hit hard...yeah, that shows how hard PoP stuff is.
<br />

<br />
65 Spell:  Veil of the Elements
<br />
Cast time: 3 sec
<br />
Reuse time: 5 minutes
<br />
Mana cost: 100 mana (I would say 60, like Jolt, but Concussion is cheaper, and mana regen for pure casters is already high)
<br />
This ability partially blinds the targeted creature in a flash of fire, reducing it's visibility of the mage, making them forget the mage in favor of other people.
<br />
Effect:  Cinder Jolt basically.  -500 hate, Fire resist.
<br />

<br />
Get it from a Spectral Rune.  You'll not find that outside of Tier 3, where you need it.  Thus, the ability is gained where it is needed.<br />_________________<br />Darlatan Firemist
<br />
60 ranger
<br />
League of Honour
<br />
Firiona Vie</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
