				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Nablzin wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I think the rogue community might have something to say about giving escape to magicians, even with a cast time =/</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>XalmatElemental wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Why? Bards have it as well, and it costs mana for them (which they can only regen thru AA and FT, and not spell effects or meditate). </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
At FanFaire, at least one rogue did pipe up and complain about this skill of Bards, especially since there was no reuse to it and, even if the bard was out of mana, die and be FM again (xps loss is trivial at 65, even if it took over 3 hours to complete the task at hand). Rogues cannot use their Escape like mashing a button every second. Considering our regen rates, and considering the absoluteness of it, the costs involved are trivial. Only the 12 minute recast timer would delay it's use.
<br />

<br />
Let's think about this though. 
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Odibil wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">The above suggestion is completely different than merely lowering you on the hatelist, it is meant to remove you from the hatelist completely, much like Feign Death, without the ability to remain feigned. 
<br />

<br />
Situations where wipes are inevitable, green-cons are scowling at you in the way of your main objective, and trash clearing becomes unnecessarily tedious, this skill would be a Godsend. Consider this the 'living' version of Feign Death, nothing more. 
<br />

<br />
However, lowering the recast time to maybe 4 minutes could make this a viable concussion spell on named encounters, come to think of it. Shoot two birds with one stone.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Feign death's aggro removal is a fixed chance, better if the mobs return to their spawn point or 'resume normal pathing' or whatever, but either way, it is only a <span style="font-style: italic">chance</span>. Only on super greenies is it an almost guaronteed, of course, assuming you didn't fail it in the first place.
<br />

<br />
Where.. exactally are you going to find this particular situation, with tons of green trash that cannot be stunned and AE'd down in order to reach a target? This 'tedious clearing' is a little misleading to me, unless you can pinpoint a place and a mob where this particular tedium takes place?
<br />

<br />
See, with a complete aggro removal, what magicians can do with this is nuke semi-hard through the general course of a fight, and when the mob gets to.. oh.. 50%, Veil themselves and proceed  to chain nuke until the mob is dead without fear of aggro. This ability is also useless to any magician high in the planes because of the simple fact that CotH is disabled near any boss mob.
<br />

<br />
Personally, I see this becomming a 'Get out of jail free' card for high level magicians on boss fights and otherwise useless or overpowering overall. It's another stab at the dark trying to solve a problem that the majority of magicians do not have.
<br />

<br />
I'm thinking if Tier 3+ magicians have issues with aggro, then perhaps a staff like enchanters have with Innorruk's Sarcasm (or a different variation thereof), like the only aggro modifying focus effect out there. Of course, drop it where it's needed, or just before, or even make it questable, though if it's questable, have it have like low stats, or not so good stats.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
