			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The mana cost is way out of line. Fading memories costs 900 mana and bards do not benefit from any sort of mana regen except FT (and MC) and are capped at a meditation of 1. Having a mage FM spell cost only 500 mana would make mages some of the best pullers in the game. Combine that with what is arguably the fastest mana regen in the game (canni pet with mana buffs/bard song) and you would have a very overpowered ability.
<br />

<br />
Mages have never had any real form of crowd control aside from our pets. This is intentional and giving us FD in any form is a bit silly. Instead change the ability like this:
<br />

<br />
-Uses 2500hp each cast. Instant casting time
<br />
-Moves you to the bottom of the aggro list (like evade used to) but does not remove you.
<br />
-Costs 900 mana
<br />

<br />
This would let you use the ability in the few situations it is really needed imo. That is very high end mages being limited by aggro over mana and not being able to contribute sufficient DPS to raids. This would let you drop your aggro on really important fights and since the chances of getting a dedicated healer just for your ghetto concusion is slim it doesn't step on the toes of wizards. It also doesn't let you pull since it won't wipe the aggro list just move you to the bottom. Lower level mages wouldn't use this ability since 2500hps would be enough to possibly put them in the low health aggro range.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
